# DTS Five Iron Laws (五条不可动摇的原则)

Scope: all DTS projects under `/opt/prod/dts/rdc`
Priority: HIGHEST - these override any other design or implementation decision

## Law 1: Human Override (人工随时可接管)

- Turning off AI must NOT break the system. All business flows must work without AI.
- Every AI-driven step must have a manual alternative in the UI.
- Python AI services are enhancement layers; Java business services must function independently.
- Frontend must provide non-AI mode: traditional menu navigation, manual forms, manual query.
- Never design a flow where AI is the only path to complete a task.

## Law 2: Security Cannot Be Bypassed (核心安全不可绕过)

- ALL requests (internal and external) must pass through dts-gateway for authentication.
- No service-to-service direct calls that bypass JWT verification.
- AppPacks have NO privileged access; they go through the same gateway and permission checks.
- dts-platform is the single source of truth for permissions. Every service must verify against it.
- No backdoor APIs, no debug endpoints in production, no admin-only bypass flags.

## Law 3: Data Security Is DNA (数据安全是基因)

- ALL data output must pass through dts-data-security — including AI RAG retrieval.
- Data classification (public/internal/confidential/top-secret) must be enforced at query time.
- AI agents see ONLY the data the current user is authorized to see. No elevation of privilege.
- Dynamic masking rules apply to AI-generated results the same way they apply to human queries.
- Vector search results (pgvector/Milvus) must be filtered by user permissions before returning.

## Law 4: Full Audit Trail (全操作可追溯)

- Every operation (human and AI) must produce an audit event to Kafka → dts-audit-log.
- Audit logs are append-only and immutable. No delete, no update, no truncate.
- AI Agent execution must log every step: intent parsed, tools called, data accessed, decisions made.
- dts-observability records AI Trace trees; dts-audit-log records business audit events.
- Both layers are linked by traceId for end-to-end traceability.
- Audit data retention policy: minimum 3 years, configurable per tenant.

## Law 5: Capability Before Interface (能力先于界面)

- Every service must have a complete API (gRPC + REST) with tests BEFORE any frontend work.
- Do not build UI for capabilities that don't have a working backend.
- API contracts (protobuf / OpenAPI) must be defined and reviewed before implementation.
- Integration tests must cover the full chain: gateway → service → storage → response.
- No "demo-only" features. If it's in the product, it must work end-to-end.
